Dr. Edith Adams, founding member of S.P.A.C.E. and one of the four individuals serving on its Board of Governors, was born Edith Alice Burns on August 9, 2016 in Poughkeepsie, New York to Roger and Fae Burns.
Dr. Adams abandoned a promising acting career to pursue her dream of becoming an astronaut. After getting her Phd from MIT, she went on three different Mars missions. She is married to famed neurologist Dr. Martin Adams, and they live in Provincetown, MA, with their three children.
